{"title_page": "Kedi (2010 film)", "text_new": "{{About||the Tamil movie directed by Jyothi Krishna and starring Ravi Krishna|Kedi (2006 film)|the Turkish documentary directed by Ceyda Torun, about street cats in Istanbul|Kedi (2016 film)}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kedi\n| image          = Kedi_(2010_film).jpg\n| caption        = Movie Poster\n| writer         = Kiran Kumar<br>{{small|(story / screenplay / dialogues)}}\n| producer       = D. Siva Prasad Reddy\n| director       = Kiran Kumar\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]]<br>[[Mamta Mohandas]] \n| music          = [[Sandeep Chowtha]]\n| cinematography = [[Sarvesh Murari]]\n| editing        = Sravan\n| studio         = [[Annapurna Studios]] & Kamakshi Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2010|2|12}}\n| runtime        = 163 mins \n| country        =  India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Kedi''''' ({{lang-en|'''Conman}}''') is a 2010 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu film]] produced by D.Sivaprasad Reddy under the Kamakshi Movies banner and directed by Kiran Kumar. The film stars [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]] and [[Mamta Mohandas]] with [[Ankur Vikal]] (''[[Slumdog Millionaire]]'') in the role of the antagonist. The music score is by [[Sandeep Chowtha]], who previously wrote music for Nagarjuna's films ''[[Ninne Pelladutha]]'' (1996), ''[[Chandralekha (1998 film)|Chandralekha]]'' (1998) and ''[[Super (2005 film)|Super]]'' (2005). The film was released on 12 February 2010. It was dubbed into Hindi as ''Gambler No. 1''. The film was recorded as a ''flop'' at the box-office.\n\n==Plot==\nRamesh, nicknamed Rummy (Nagarjuna) loves his childhood friend Janaki, who asks him to become rich and powerful before marrying her. With this motive, Rummy starts gambling and becomes rich in no time.\n\nACP Sekhar (Sayaji Shinde) notice his activities and attempts to catch him. Rummy moves to Goa where he meets Chandra (Ankur), a pub owner who also runs gambling. Both of them make a deal. While on the task, Rummy rescues Sara (Paula) from Victor. Sara\u2019s sister Nadia (Linda) falls in love with him. Another woman, Sandhya (Mamta Mohandas), enters his life. She helps him in his task. Meanwhile, differences arise between Rummy and Chandra, and they become rivals. How Rummy encounters the situation with Janaki forms the rest of the story<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telugu.16reels.com/movies/Kedi-Movie_Details_Synopsis_Cast_Crew.aspx |title=Kedi - movie details, cast and crew, star cast, review, cast and crew details, actors, director |publisher=Telugu.16reels.com |date= |accessdate=10 November 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007184705/http://telugu.16reels.com/movies/Kedi-Movie_Details_Synopsis_Cast_Crew.aspx |archivedate= 7 October 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n* [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]] as Ramesh \"Rummy\"\n* [[Mamta Mohandas]] as Janaki / Sandhya\n* [[Ankur Vikal]] as Chandra\n* [[Sayaji Shinde]] as ACP Shekar\n* [[Kelly Dorji]] as Victor\n* [[Brahmanandam]] as Six Foot\n* [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]] as Rummy's sidekick\n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Rummy's father\n* [[Harsha Vardhan]] as Rummy's partner in crime\n* [[Linda Arsenio]] as Nadia\n* [[Akhilendra Mishra]] as Shailendra\n* [[Stunt Silva]]\n* [[Anushka Shetty]] in an item number  \n* [[Mahek Chahal]] in an item number\n* Kamal \n* Sukul Dev   \n* Nirmal Pandy \n* Selva \n* Manto \n* Radha Krishna \n* Koteswara Rao \n* Anji \n* Sridhar \n* Swami \n* Sivan \n* Paanla \n* Salmar Suresh \n* Srinivas Vajpai \n* Kalyan Bhupathi \n* Dham\n* Pavala Shyamala \n* Jayavani\n* Shanthi \n* Aparna \n* Padma Reddy \n* Shilpa \n* Kalpana Chowdary \n* Mattisri \n* Master Srinivas Sai as Childhood Ramesh\n* Master Fayaak\n* Master Swethik \n* Master Bulbul \n* Baby Predela Manjula \n* Baby Yaani\n}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Kedi\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Sandeep Chowtha]]\n| cover      = Kedi film.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2009\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 37:20\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = [[Sandeep Chowtha]]\n| prev_title = [[Saleem (film)|Saleem]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = Mitti\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\nThe music was composed by [[Sandeep Chowtha]]. Music released by ADITYA Music Company.\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed =\n| headline =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 37:20\n| all_writing =\n| all_lyrics =\n| all_music =\n| title1  = Kedigaadu\n| lyrics1 = Chinni Charan\n| extra1  = [[Sunidhi Chauhan]] \n| length1 = 3:47\n\n| title2  = Neeve Na Neeve Na\n| lyrics2 = Chinni Charan\n| extra2  = [[Arijit Singh]], [[Neha Kakkar]]\n| length2 = 5:34\n\n| title3  = Enduko Enthaki\n| lyrics3 = Chinni Charan\n| extra3  = Saleem Shahida\n| length3 = 5:29\n\n| title4  = Relarey\n| lyrics4 = Chinni Charan\n| extra4  = [[Sonu Kakkar]]  \n| length4 = 4:57\n\n| title5  = Short And Sweet \n| lyrics5 = Krishna Chaitanya\n| extra5  = [[Sandeep Chowtha]]\n| length5 = 5:04\n\n| title6  = Neelo Yemunnado  \n| lyrics6 = Chinni Charan\n| extra6  = [[Rahul Nambiar]] \n| length6 = 4:08\n\n| title7  = Jaaniya Jaane \n| lyrics7 = Sandeep Chowtha\n| extra7  = Neha Kakkar\n| length7 = 5:02\n\n| title8  = Muddante \n| lyrics8 = Chinni Charan\n| extra8  = [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]], [[Geetha Madhuri]] \n| length8 = 4:03\n\n| title9  = Kedigaadu (Orchestra) \n| lyrics9 = Chinni Charan\n| extra9  = Sunidhi Chauhan\n| length9 = 3:06 \n}}\n\n==Production==\nThe film went through a series of name changes in production from ''Rummy'' to ''Mayagadu'' to ''Mosagadu'', before the producers agreed on ''Kedi''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/functions/pressmeet-kedi.html |title=Kedi Press meet - Telugu cinema function - Nagarjuna & Mamata Mohandas |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=30 November 2009 |accessdate=10 November 2011}}</ref>  A Tamil dubbed version of the movie was also released, entitled ''Singa Vettai''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kochiservnet.com/movies/theatre.php?id=Singa%20Vettai&page=0 |title=Movie Buzz - Singa Vettai - Reviews, Running Theaters, Show Times in Kochi/Cochin |publisher=Kochiservnet.com |date=24 October 2010 |accessdate=10 November 2011}}</ref>\nThe film was also dubbed in Hindi as ''Gambler No 1''. The video clip of the song \u201cNeeve Na Neeve Na\" was shot in [[Milos Island]] in Greece.<ref>[https://elinepa.org/kedi-2010-telugu-film/ Kedi (2010 Telugu Film)], 2003</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|1582524|Kedi}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kedi}}\n[[Category:2010 films]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian action comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Goa]]\n[[Category:Films set in Goa]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Sandeep Chowta]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films dubbed in Hindi]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films dubbed in Tamil]]\n", "text_old": "{{About||the Tamil movie directed by Jyothi Krishna and starring Ravi Krishna|Kedi (2006 film)|the Turkish documentary directed by Ceyda Torun, about street cats in Istanbul|Kedi (2016 film)}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kedi\n| image          = Kedi_(2010_film).jpg\n| caption        = Movie Poster\n| writer         = Kiran Kumar<br>{{small|(story / screenplay / dialogues)}}\n| producer       = D. Siva Prasad Reddy\n| director       = Kiran Kumar\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]]<br>[[Mamta Mohandas]] \n| music          = [[Sandeep Chowtha]]\n| cinematography = [[Sarvesh Murari]]\n| editing        = Sravan\n| studio         = [[Annapurna Studios]] & Kamakshi Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2010|2|12}}\n| runtime        = 163 mins \n| country        =  India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Kedi''''' ({{lang-en|Conman}}) is a 2010 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language [[action film]] produced by D.Sivaprasad Reddy under the Kamakshi Movies banner and directed by Kiran Kumar. The film stars [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]] and [[Mamta Mohandas]] with [[Ankur Vikal]] (''[[Slumdog Millionaire]]'') in the role of the antagonist. The music score is by [[Sandeep Chowtha]], who previously wrote music for Nagarjuna's films ''[[Ninne Pelladutha]]'' (1996), ''[[Chandralekha (1998 film)|Chandralekha]]'' (1998) and ''[[Super (2005 film)|Super]]'' (2005). The film was released on 12 February 2010.\n\n==Plot==\nRamesh, nickname Rummy (Nagarjuna) loves his childhood friend Janaki, who asks him to become rich and powerful before marrying her. With this motive, Rummy starts gambling and becomes rich in no time.\n\nACP Sekhar (Shayaji Shinde) notice his activities and attempts to catch him. Rummy moves to Goa where he meets Chandra (Ankur), a pub owner who also runs gambling. Both of them make a deal. While on the task, Rummy rescues Sara (Paula) from Victor. Sara's sister Nadia (Linda) falls in love with him. Another woman, Sandhya (Mamta Mohandas), enters his life. She helps him in his task. Meanwhile, differences arise between Rummy and Chandra, and they become rivals. How Rummy encounters the situation with Janaki forms the rest of the story<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telugu.16reels.com/movies/Kedi-Movie_Details_Synopsis_Cast_Crew.aspx |title=Kedi - movie details, cast and crew, star cast, review, cast and crew details, actors, director |publisher=Telugu.16reels.com |accessdate=10 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007184705/http://telugu.16reels.com/movies/Kedi-Movie_Details_Synopsis_Cast_Crew.aspx |archivedate= 7 October 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==