ations on a Hindu Deity|last=Beck|first=Guy L. (Ed.)|authorlink=Guy Beck|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0SJ73GHSCF8C|publisher=SUNY Press|year=2005|isbn=0-7914-6415-6|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|author=Matchett, Freda|title=Krsna, Lord or Avatara? the relationship between Krsna and Visnu: in the context of the Avatara myth as presented by the Harivamsa, the Visnupurana and the Bhagavatapurana|publisher=Routledge|location=Surrey|year=2000|pages=254|isbn=0-7007-1281-X|oclc=|doi=}}\n*{{cite book|author=Valpey, Kenneth Russell|title=Attending {{IAST|K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a}}'s image: {{IAST|Caitanya Vai\u1e63\u1e47ava m\u016brti-sev\u0101}} as devotional truth\n|publisher=Routledge\n|location=New York\n|year=2006\n|pages=\n|isbn=0-415-38394-3\n|oclc=\n|doi=\n}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book|author=Ganguli, K.M.|year=1896|title=Bhagavad-Gita ([http://www.sacred-texts.com/hin/m06/m06025.htm XXV]-[http://www.sacred-texts.com/hin/m06/m06042.htm XLII]). [http://www.sacred-texts.com/hin/maha/index.htm The Mahabharata], Book 6|publisher=Calcutta: Bharata Press|isbn=}}\n* {{cite book|author=A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Prabhup\u0101da|year=1988|title=\u015ar\u012bmad-Bh\u0101gavatam (Bh\u0101gavata Pur\u0101\u1e47a)|url=http://www.vedabase.com/en/sb/|publisher=The Bhaktivedanta Book Trust|isbn=}}\n* {{cite book|author=A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Prabhup\u0101da|year=1972|title=Bhagavad-g\u012bt\u0101 As It Is|url=http://www.vedabase.com/en/bg/|publisher=The Bhaktivedanta Book Trust|isbn=}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.stephen-knapp.com/sri_krishna.htm Sri Krishna - Differences in Realisation & Perception of the Supreme] (stephen-knapp.com)\n\n{{Krishna|state=collapsed}}\n{{Vaishnava philosophy}}\n{{Names of God}}\n\n[[Category:Krishna]]\n[[Category:Vaishnavism]]\n[[Category:Hindu philosophical concepts]]\n[[Category:Gaudiya Vaisnava philosophical concepts]]\n[[Category:Titles and names of Krishna]]\n[[Category:Names of God in Hinduism]]\n", "name_user": "223